Name: Oleksandr Kostyliev
Background: Oleksandr “s1mple” Kostyliev was born on October 2, 1997 and is currently inactive on the Natus Vincere roster. s1mple is considered by many to be the best Counter-Strike player of all time, a claim that is supported by his many achievements and trophies. His teams have won a Major, an Intel Grand Slam, and many top tier tournaments, while his personal accolades include over 20 HLTV MVP medals, and the number one position in HLTV’s ‘best player of the year’ lists. He was the runner-up in 2019 and 2020.s1mple has played for many teams, including Liquid, FlipSid3, and HellRaisers, but has won most tournaments with Natus Vincere, where he joined in August of 2016.

He has won multiple MVP awards, and has come close to winning HLTV’s best player of the year award (coming in third in 2021 and 2018, and second in 2017).His cousin, Nemanja “huNter-” Kovač, is also a professional Counter-Strike 2 player.

Name: Can Dörtkardeş
Background: Can “XANTARES” Dörtkardeş is a Turkish professional Counter-Strike 2 player, and is currently playing for Eternal Fire as a rifler. XANTARES is a very popular player, in part due to the fact that he has the ‘XANTARES peek’ named after him. This is a way of peeking where a player wide peeks (thus moving past the angle that an enemy might be holding) and then shoots the enemy almost instantly due to near perfect crosshair placement.

Name: Adil Benrlitom
Background: Adil “ScreaM” Benrlitom is a professional VALORANT player from Belgium who is currently playing for Karmine Corp. ScreaM started his professional gaming career as a pro Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player, where he achieved great successes with teams such as G2, VeryGames, and EnVyUs. He was one of the top 10 CS:GO players in the world in 2013 and 2016, and became known for his tap-focused playstyle that relied heavily on getting headshots, earning him the nickname ‘headshot machine’. He was and still is a very popular player, in part thanks to his mechanical ability and entertaining playstyle.At the end of 2020, he switched to VALORANT and joined Team Liquid.
